Re: "Freely" translated
by furrykef » Wed 06.29.2011 1:54 am I'm a big fan of translating freely and I do it myself. The problem, of course, is that it's easy to get lazy and not bother fully understanding the original text because you can BS your way through it. But a translator really is something of a second writer, and I think sometimes it's his job to distill something to its essence rather than slavishly duplicate the original work. For instance, I love the Pioneer/Geneon dub of Lupin III even though it takes massive liberties with it -- obviously, there were no jokes about Shaq or eBay in the 70s. But it's funny, and that's the important thing.
Founder of Learning Languages Through Video Games.Also see my lang-8 journal, where you can help me practice Japanese (and Spanish, and Italian!)
